    "Suppose X is compact and k ∈ N. For any current T ∈ D k (X), |T (f, π 1,..., π k)| ≤ ∥T ∥ C(K) ∥f ∥ L k j=1 Lip(π j), for every (f, π 1,..., π 1) ∈ Lip b (X) × [Lip(X)] k.Proof.",
    "By locality, we may subtract constant maps from each of the last d variables of T. Thus, it is sufficient to prove the inequality assuming π 1,..., π d ∈ Lip 0 (X).",
    "By homogeneity in each variable (on both sides of the inequality), it is sufficient to prove the statement under the additional assumption that (f, π 1,..., π k) ∈ K(X).",
    "Then the statement holds by definition of ∥T ∥ C(K).",
